      "writtenOn": "2019-08-30T20:48:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Given that the return behavior should be the same in three cases, what I’d suggest for structuring this entire function is:\n\n  if (initialized_.is_valid() \u0026\u0026 flush_needed_) {\n    flush_needed_ \u003d false;\n    int result \u003d Z_OK;\n    do {\n      // …\n    } while (result !\u003d Z_STREAM_END);\n  }\n\n  return output_stream_-\u003eFlush();\n\nThat makes it much more likely that output_stream_-\u003eFlush() will be called in every desirable situation, even as the code is maintained and modified.",
      "revId": "29054e21471b9a31439cc12574f7126f1716a4f2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
